comment: A "local" form of ~ gchac . If ` A ` and ` ~P A ` are GCH-sets, then the Hartogs number of ` A ` is ` ~P A ` (so ` ~P A ` and a fortiori ` A ` are well-orderable). The proof is due to Specker. Theorem 2.1 of [KanamoriPincus] p. 419. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 31-May-2015.)
